A number of people are injured in a clash that broke out among traders at Ilepo Oke Odo market in Lagos. A Daily Trust correspondent at the scene says the clash is between Yoruba and Hausa traders at the market. The clash has caused holdup at Iyana Ipaja- Abule Egba road, and on other roads linking to Ilepo Oke Odo.  2 Kwara monarchs to forfeit 3 months salaries over clash Ghana, Nigeria traders clash in Accra market Ramadan: Prices of tomatoes, pepper increase by 60% in Lagos Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin